miscConds.notes: Restitution to be repaid in monthly increments of no less than $100 starting the first day of the month on full month after release from custody. Case Called @ 1:29 PM: Defendant Gary L. Tracy in court, appearing pro se via video from JCI.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Agent Ashley Struzynski in court, appearing via telephone.  Court convenes today for a hearing to discuss further the petition for civil judgment due to the very specific repayment schedule that was ordered on restitution.  Argument by ADA for extension of supervision.  A further period of concurrent supervision would not be a detriment to Defendant.  Court advises Def of right to counsel.  Statement by Def as to length of incarceration.  Def states he is willing to proceed today without counsel and expects to be released to ERP in the next 5-6 mos.  Statement by Agent - believes that the reason Petition was forwarded was due to language on JOC for civil judgment.  Court extends supervision for a period of 1 yr from today's date.  The monthly $100 restitution payment previously ordered to be made beginning with the first month following his release from incarceration.  If Def has the ability to pay in full court would gladly entertain a request for early termination.  Civil Judgment declined by the Court.
